"Don't want to."

02:15.360 --> 02:18.880
It was one of those
booths in the arcade.

02:18.880 --> 02:22.560
Can't imagine how excited we kids
were, getting a record in the mail

02:22.560 --> 02:24.760
from Atlantic City recorded
by Mom and Dad!

02:24.760 --> 02:27.480
It's just a little family joke,
no reason you should get it.

02:27.480 --> 02:29.440
It's kind of funny.

02:29.440 --> 02:30.840
Have you still got the record?

02:30.840 --> 02:32.200
Somewhere.

02:32.200 --> 02:34.280
I think I'll go get a cigarette.
Care to join me?

02:34.280 --> 02:35.560
He quit, Dad.

02:35.560 --> 02:36.960
Oh.

02:36.960 --> 02:38.720
Hey, good for you.

02:38.720 --> 02:41.480
I quit too, it was right
after Gary here was born.

02:41.480 --> 02:44.240
And after Joan was born
and Roger and Sam and Tommy.

02:44.240 --> 02:46.480
Will ya?

02:46.480 --> 02:49.080
After all, I like smoking too.

02:49.080 --> 02:51.200
I could use some air.

02:51.200 --> 02:53.960
OK, follow me.

02:53.960 --> 02:55.000
Shirley.

02:55.000 --> 02:58.720
Hello, Doc.
How are you, you son of a gun?

02:58.720 --> 03:02.240
Doc Bogart, I want you
to meet Bob Caldwell.

03:02.240 --> 03:03.440
He is a real doctor.

03:03.440 --> 03:04.920
What kind of medicine you in?

03:04.920 --> 03:06.040
Plastic surgeon.

03:06.040 --> 03:08.720
Do me a favour.
Stop by my table later,

03:08.720 --> 03:11.600
